      <h2><u>Home (Intro)</u></h2>
      <p>Within this webpage you will be able to read and interact with the content/links. The content/links within this webpage will give you an opportunity to learn more about myself and my current experience as a Correlation One student. If you are intrigued and want a chance to sign up and learn more please provide your contact information below. </p>
      <h2><u>About Me</u></h2>
      <p>My name is Donte Hill. I am 24 years old and the youngest of 3 children. I was raised in China Grove, NC where I found my passion for sports. With plans to stay involved in sports as I grew up, I continued my education at <a href="https://news.ecu.edu/2020/11/30/great-sport/" target="_blank">East Carolina University</a> and recieved my bachelor's degree in Sports Studies with a minor in Psychology. I graduated during the pandemic and that had an affect on my plans for sports, but it ultimately lead me to Amazon and into a new interest for technology.</p>
      <h2><u>Blog</u></h2>
      <p>Following graduation, I began working at Amazon in May of 2021 as a picker. While working as a picker I had the opportunity to become a learning ambassador & progress to a learning trainer in August of 2022. As I continue to develop within my career, I am happy to be a part of Correlation One. Since joining Correlation One I have had an opportunity to be hands on and build on the prior knowledge that I gained on HTML through <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/?messages=success%5B0%5D%3Dflash.signin-success" target="_blank">freecodecamp.org </a>. The most interesting and challenging thing that I have learned so far is formatting (spacing and alignments) and making sure that I can format or structure my content to my liking but also make it easily accessible to viewers.
    </div>
